Walking Eye Mobile app Privacy Policy
Insight Guides Privacy Policy
Your privacy and the security and integrity of your personal information is very important to Insight Guides! This Privacy Policy (this “Policy”) describes how Apa Digital AG, Siebnen (Switzerland), a corporation established under the laws of Switzerland with a principal address of Bahnhofplatz 6, CH-8854 Siebnen and being registered in the Commercial Register of the Canton of Schwyz, registration number CH20.3033.676, d/b/a Insight Guides (“Insight Guides,” or “we” or “us” or similar construction) handles any information ("Information") which you may provide in respect of your use of our “Walking Eye” App or our Website ww.insightguides.com ().
We may revise this Privacy Policy (a "Revised Policy") at any time without notice to you (unless otherwise required by law) by posting the Revised Policy in the App or on the Website. Such Revised Policy shall be effective as to all use of the App or the Website and all Information provided from and after their posting. The Revised Policy shall also apply to Information submitted prior to such revision to the extent permitted by applicable law. Your sole remedy should you disagree with any portion of the Revised Policy shall be to cease to use the App or the Website.
Approval of Policy; Scope
By viewing, using, or otherwise interacting with the App and Website, you agree to be bound by the rules applicable of this Policy. If you do not agree to it and/or any part of this Privacy Policy, please do not use the App, Website or any other service offered electronically by Insight Guides. Please note that there are some areas which you may use without any required login credentials and without the requirement that you establish an account or otherwise reveal your identity.
If you provide the Information of any other person to us, you hereby represent and warrant that you are authorized by such person (or his or her parent or legal guardian) to provide such Information for our purposes as provided herein. Minors may not submit purchase requests and should not provide any Information to the App or the Website without the preceding consent of their parents or their guardian. Should a minor although submit a purchase request it is assumed that either his parents or guardian have not supervised him or her properly and that they become liable as outlined in the Terms and Conditions and Art 333 Swss Civil Code.
This Privacy Policy does not cover (1) any ideas or suggestions you may submit for the App or Website; (2) any information you submit in the form of social media, blogs, responses to comments, reviews or user opinion, and any other content you submit with the apparent intention that such information is published or displayed in the App or on the Website, each of which we may use for any purposes in our sole discretion without limitation. We recommend that you do not include any personal, financial, health, or other sensitive information in any such user reviews, comments, or other social media posting or content, as that information may be published and publicly available; (3) any anonymized data.
The limits of liability and disclaimers outlined in our Terms and Conditions [link this] also apply to our liability and responsibility under this Privacy Policy.
Collection and Retention of Information
Subject to the disclosures made in this Privacy Policy, we will not collect any Information without your knowledge and your preceding consent. In order to use many of the features in the App or on the Website, you are required to create a user profile and provide secure login credentials (including username/email and password). By creating your user profile, you consent to our storage, use, and another handling of the information you provide for the purposes described in this Privacy Policy and as may otherwise be permitted by applicable law.
In addition, from time to time Insight Guides may request information via surveys or contests.
Participation in these surveys or contests is completely voluntary, and you have a choice whether or not to disclose this information. In addition to any use of the information described in this Privacy Policy, information collected during surveys and contests will be used for the purposes specified on the forms on which it is collected. Except as described herein, we will not sell your Information to third parties for their promotional activities unrelated to the purposes for which your information was submitted.
Use of Information by Insight Guides
In addition to the other uses described in this Policy, we use your Information to:
- Validate your identity and regulate access to your account and various App or Website features;
- Diagnose technical problems and allocate the resources of our systems, including measuring the use of the App or Website;
- Personalize your experience with the App or Website and improve our content;
- Provide user support and to contact you for administrative purposes relating to your account, or to provide you support in response to your queries; please note that additional Information may be collected from or in response to your query (name, mailing address or email address and billing information) and other information necessary to assist you;
- Compile information related to your queries, keywords, and phrases generally;
- Provide information pertaining to Insight Guides’ services which may be of interest to you, [on an opt-out basis];
- Distribute an Insight Guides newsletter and other promotional communications [on an opt-out basis]. We use reasonable efforts to assure that promotional communications include appropriate security to the extent your computer or mobile internet access device is capable of such security. You may unsubscribe to any of our promotional communications at any time; and/or
- Create aggregate and anonymous demographic or other information which we may use for any purpose once decoupled from your personal or financial information (such as to assist our advertisers in choosing ad space or tracking campaigns).
Provision of Information to Third Parties
Except as provided herein, we will not disclose your Information to third parties. We do share your Personal Information as necessary to fulfil your requests or to enable certain functions or features in the App or on the Website. For details related to information necessary to process bookings check Webpage Privacy Policy (
https://www.insightguides.com/static_page/insight-guides-privacy-policy
).
Deletion of Your Personal Account
If you wish your Information to be modified or deleted, you may access much of your Information yourself through the App or the Website for such purpose. Please email us at hello@insightguides.com (hello@insightguides.com) if you have any questions or
would like any information which you cannot access modified or deleted, and we will use commercially reasonable efforts to do so, provided that this may result in your inability to use or access certain functions or features on the Website.
Please note that some of your Information may remain in our secure backups even if we are able to delete it from our production systems and that we may not be able to honour your request if we are legally obliged to retain that information.
Other Events
All information collected or provided may be transferred or assigned by Insight Guides in conjunction with a merger or the sale of all or a
a portion of Insight Guides (or similar events).
Questions
Should you have a query on our Privacy Policy please contact us:
Apa Digital AG Bahnhofplatz 6 CH-8854 Siebnen.
www.insightguides.com (/)
Applicable Law and Jurisdiction
This Privacy Policy shall be governed by and construed in accordance with Swiss material law. Any disputes arising between any App user or Website user and Insight Guides in connection to this Privacy Policy shall exclusively be submitted to the competent Ordinary Courts at Lachen (Switzerland).
